# 📈 Regression Analysis (Linear Regression)

## 🔍 Overview

This project applies Linear Regression to model relationships between dependent and independent variables and predict continuous outcomes.

## 📊 Model Performance

* R² Score: ~0.60 – 0.75 (moderate explanatory power)
* Adjusted R²: slightly lower, indicating some irrelevant variables
* Model statistically significant (p < 0.05)

## 📈 Key Findings

* Strong positive relationship observed between key predictors and target variable
* Some variables showed low statistical significance and were removed
* Multicollinearity detected and reduced using feature selection

## 📉 Error Metrics

* RMSE used to evaluate prediction error
* Residuals showed near-normal distribution (valid model assumptions)

## 💡 Insights

* Model explains a significant portion of variance but not fully predictive
* Feature selection improved model performance
* Suitable for baseline prediction and trend analysis

## 📌 Conclusion

Linear Regression effectively captured relationships in the dataset, but improvements can be made using advanced models.
